01-Sep-06

Here is a very good MiamiDX configuration that I hope will boost your
internet transfer rate a lot, as it did for my connection.


@{b}Story@{ub}
I have an A1200 with a PCMCIA Genius ME3000II eth card (I use
cnet.device) connected to a LAN network that ends with a router\ADSL
modem. Well, I noticed my Win PC was always much faster in dloading
so one day I tried to play a bit with MiamiDX SysCtl page, and this
config was born ;)
It's not a mistery MiamiDX's config was created with very old hardware
in mind so the SysCtl prefs page reflects these obsolete settings
unsuitable for Y2006 connections...
Before I had a ~80KB/s speed, now it reaches ~150+!

@{b}Beware!@{ub}
For some HW\\SW users' config, without an external fast DNS server,
these parameters can be changed to their previous MiamiDX defaults:
@{u}New@{uu}					@{u}Old@{uu}
dns.cache.size 64			32
dns.cache.flush 0			 0
dns.cache.enabled 0			 1
dns.cache.split 1			 1/0

@{b}How to use them@{ub}
Very simple, you can import the SysCtl.txt directly into MiamiDX.
To do so just press RMB on the Database/SysCtl prefs page and
import from ASCII file...
If not, you can always check values one by one by hand! :)

Greetings to all my friends, and #amigazeux, #amigaita etc. etc.
